<item>
            <title>[HBASE-11206] Enable automagically tweaking memstore and blockcache sizes</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-11206</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-5349&quot; title=&quot;Automagically tweak global memstore and block cache sizes based on workload&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-5349&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-5349&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;Automagically tweak global memstore and block cache sizes based on workload&quot; adds a nice new feature. It is off by default.  Lets turn it on for 0.99.  Liang Xie is concerned that automatically shifting blockcache and memstore sizes could wreck havoc w/ GC&apos;ing in low-latency serving situation &amp;#8211; a valid concern &amp;#8211; but lets enable this feature in 0.99 and see how it does.  Can always disable it before 1.0 if a problem.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12715326">HBASE-11206</key>
